馬來西亞是相對開放的以國家利益為導向與[[新興工業化國家|新興工業化]][[市场经济|市場經濟體]]<ref>{{cite web |last = Boulton |first = WilliaM |last2 = Pecht |first2 = Michael |last3 = Tucker |first3 = William |last4 = Wennberg |first4 = Sam |url = http://www.wtec.org/loyola/em/04_07.htm |title = Electronics Manufacturing in the Pacific Rim, World Technology Evaluation Center, Chapter 4: Malaysia |publisher = Wtec.org |date = 1997年5月 |accessdate = 2010-11-01 |deadurl = yes |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20101215111543/http://www.wtec.org/loyola/em/04_07.htm |archivedate = 2010-12-15 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.infernalramblings.com/articles/Malaysian_Economy/436/ |title=Malaysia, A Statist Economy |publisher=Infernalramblings.com |accessdate=2010-11-01 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101007104445/http://www.infernalramblings.com/articles/Malaysian_Economy/436/ |archivedate=2010-10-07 }}</ref>。國家透過宏觀經濟計劃，在指引經濟活動上發揮了重要作用，但其重要性逐漸下降。馬來西亞擁有亞洲最佳的經濟紀錄，[[國內生產總值|國內生產總值]]從1957至2005年，每年平均增長6.5%<ref name="state.gov"/>。2007年，馬來西亞是[[東南亞|東南亞]]第二大經濟體，並且依據[[購買力平價|購買力平價]]是[[各国国内生产总值列表_(购买力平价)|全球第29位的經濟體]]，國內生產總值淨額在2008年是2,220億美元<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.google.com/publicdata?ds=wb-wdi&met=ny_gdp_mktp_cd&idim=country:MYS&dl=en&hl=en&q=malaysian+gdp |title=Public data |publisher=Google |accessdate=2010-09-27 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111001193940/http://www.google.com/publicdata?ds=wb-wdi |archivedate=2011-10-01 }}</ref>。2007年之後，維持5%－7%的成長率<ref>{{Cite news| title=Malaysia resilient against global economic slump| url=http://www.theedgedaily.com/cms/content.jsp?id=com.tms.cms.article.Article_7a3ef830-cb73c03a-c1186f00-95cc4df1| publisher=The Edge| author=| accessdate=2008-04-23| archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080429190542/http://www.theedgedaily.com/cms/content.jsp?id=com.tms.cms.article.Article_7a3ef830-cb73c03a-c1186f00-95cc4df1| archivedate=2008-04-29| deadurl=yes}}</ref>。2009的國民平均所得是14,900美元<ref name="CIA Fact Book"/>。2009年的國內生產總值是3,836億美元，每人平均國內生產總值是8,100美元<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook/rankorder/2001rank.html |title=COUNTRY COMPARISON :: GDP (PURCHASING POWER PARITY) |publisher=CIA |accessdate=2010-10-26 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110604195034/https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook/rankorder/2001rank.html |archivedate=2011-06-04 }}</ref>。

