傳統上，馬來西亞的能源生產主要依靠煤炭、石油與天然氣<ref name="Unimap">{{cite web |url=http://publicweb.unimap.edu.my/~ppkas/home/index.php/news/articles/29-renewable-energy-and-kyoto-protocol-adoption-in-malaysia |title=Renewable Energy and Kyoto Protocol: Adoption in Malaysia |publisher=Universiti Malaysia Perlis |accessdate=2010-09-24 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100430012655/http://publicweb.unimap.edu.my/~ppkas/home/index.php/news/articles/29-renewable-energy-and-kyoto-protocol-adoption-in-malaysia |archivedate=2010-04-30 }}</ref>。該國目前具有13GW的發電能力<ref name="GENI">{{cite web |author=Global Energy Network Institute |url=http://www.geni.org/globalenergy/library/national_energy_grid/malaysia/index.shtml |title=National Energy Grid of Malaysia – National Electricity Transmission Grid of Malaysia |publisher=Global Energy Network Institute |date=2007-06-28 |accessdate=2010-09-24 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100529090850/http://www.geni.org/globalenergy/library/national_energy_grid/malaysia/index.shtml |archivedate=2010-05-29 }}</ref>。然而，馬來西亞的天然氣儲量只剩下33年，石油儲量只剩下19年。為因應這個情況，馬來西亞政府正致力於可再生能源<ref name="Unimap"/>目前的發電量有16%來自水力發電，其餘84%來自火力發電。<ref name="GENI"/>。石油及天然氣工業目前由國營石油公司[[国油|国油]]所掌控<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.eia.gov/emeu/cabs/Malaysia/pdf.pdf |title=Malaysia |publisher=United States Energy Information Administration |date=2010年12月 |accessdate=2011-06-10 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111003141602/http://www.eia.gov/emeu/cabs/Malaysia/pdf.pdf |archivedate=2011-10-03 }}</ref>，而且整個能源部門由{{link-en|馬來西亞能源委员会|Energy Commission of Malaysia}}所管理，這是依據2001年能源委员会法所成立，掌管半島及沙巴的能源<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.st.gov.my/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=2388&Itemid=1689 |title=Overview of Energy Commission |publisher=Suruhanjaya Tenaga (Energy Commission) |accessdate=2010-09-24 |archive-date=2021-01-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210115124109/https://www.st.gov.my//index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=2388&Itemid=1689 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

